{
  "texts": [
    "The results demonstrate a consistent and substantial accuracy improvement of A-Learn with six different models after model customization with domain-specific data.",
    "The accuracy improvement ranges from 2.7% to 24.3% and the average is 16.8%.",
    "This validates our hypothesis that incorporating domain-specific knowledge into existing models can boost the model's performance in adult learning sentiment analysis.",
    "Notably, A-Learn based on Twitter-RoBERTa reaches an accuracy of 91.3%, with a big increase from 76.3% when Twitter-RoBERTa is not customized.",
    "This underscores the importance of customizing the base models with the data of a similar format (e.g., from Twitter) for sentiment analysis.A-Learn is also efficient."
  ]
}